 The road is still closed after a shootout between robbers and the Police in the early ours of this morning. At 1:30 information was received of about twenty men planning to bomb ATMs at Mhluzi.
The operational team went to the area. Upon arrival they found a group of criminals had already bombed one business. There was gun exchange with Fidelity security
The suspects were in four vehicles, a silver Volkswagen Polo, a blue Polo, ST Ford and red BMW 1 series. Upon arrival the team were greeted with heavy fire from AK47, R5 rifles and a pistol The Police returned fire and the suspects fled in a Ford and Volkswagen Polo.
Three occupants in the Polo were killed in the shootout. The BMW lost control and four men got out of the car and shot at the Police with AK47 rifles. They fled into the bushes on the R555.
No member of the Police or security company is injured. Members of the K9 unit are busy searching for the robbers in the bushes.  Suspects might be linked to seven other robberies • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za